{"key":"processedPost-16941278","value":{"id":16941278,"first":16908930,"last":16942977,"when":1349060318,"utime":"10/01/12 05:58 AM","content":"Misting cakes directly doesn't cause aborts and misting the sides of a shotgun terrarium is a waste of water which also makes it hard to see your cakes.&nbsp; In the early days when people were using sealed up tubs for terrariums, they had to keep water off the cakes and pins because with no fresh air the water droplets wouldn't evaporate and would lead to blotch and other problems, including aborting pins.<br /><br />However, misting pins directly in a shotgun terrarium won't abort them because they'll be dry in half an hour.&nbsp; You should be misting your cakes several times daily until they glisten to keep them hydrated.<br />RR","title":"Re: SGFC problem.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}